.container
  .flex.flex-col.w-full
    .border.border-primary.rounded-lg.lg:p-10.p-5.my-12.md:my-24
      %div{class: 'flex items-center justify-center'}
        %div{class: 'w-[%80] md:w-[50%]'}
          %div{ class: "flex items-center justify-center text-secondary text-[2rem] font-lato font-bold mb-5"} 
            Privacy Policy
          .flex.flex-col.items-start.justify-start.text-left
            %p
              Chesed Train Inc. (referred to as "Chesed Train," "we," "us," or "our"), is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and safeguard your information as a nonprofit organization focused on delivering organized support to those in need.
          .flex.flex-col.items-start.justify-start.text-left
            %div{ class: "text-secondary lg:text-[1.8rem] text-[1.8rem] font-lato font-normal my-5"} 
              Information We Collect
            %ul
              %li.my-3
                <b>Personal Information:</b> We collect personal details such as your name, email, and contact information when you sign up, participate in an event, or donate. This information is used to facilitate our services and manage our community interactions.
              %li.my-3
                <b>Donation Information:</b> As a nonprofit, we carefully handle donor information, ensuring it is used strictly for processing donations and communicating with you about your contributions.
              %li.my-3
                <b>Cookies and Tracking:</b> We use cookies and similar technologies to enhance your experience on our site and track usage patterns, helping us improve our services.
              %li.my-3
                <b>Information from Communications:</b> If you contact us for support or with questions, we may keep records of that correspondence, including any personal information shared during the communication. This helps us improve our customer service and address your concerns more effectively.
          .flex.flex-col.items-start.justify-start.text-left
            %div{ class: "text-secondary lg:text-[1.8rem] text-[1.8rem] font-lato font-normal my-5"} 
              How We Use Your Information
            %ul
              %li.my-3
                <b>Service Provision:</b> Your information allows us to effectively coordinate support activities, such as meal deliveries, event planning, and fundraising efforts, in line with our mission to deliver kindness.
              %li.my-3
                <b>Communication:</b> We use your contact details to keep you informed about Chesed Train’s activities, updates, and opportunities for further involvement.
              %li.my-3
                <b>Charitable Activities:</b> A portion of proceeds from donations and fundraising efforts supports various charitable causes, as part of our mission as a Chesed organization.
              %li.my-3
                <b>Promotional Communications:</b> We may use your information to send you promotional materials about our programs, events, and other ways to support Chesed Train’s mission. You can opt out of these communications at any time.
              %li.my-3
                <b>Advertisements:</b> We may work with third-party service providers to display advertisements on our website. These providers may use cookies, web beacons, or similar technologies to collect information about your online activities on our site and other websites. This information helps us deliver more relevant ads and gauge the effectiveness of our advertising efforts.
          .flex.flex-col.items-start.justify-start.text-left
            %div{ class: "text-secondary lg:text-[1.8rem] text-[1.8rem] font-lato font-normal my-5"} 
              Data Sharing
            %p
              We do not sell your personal information. However, we may share it with trusted partners who assist in our operations, such as payment processing for donations. These partners are required to protect your information and use it only for the purposes specified by Chesed Train.
            %p
              We may also share information if required by law, or to protect our rights and the safety of our users, including cooperating with authorities in legal investigations.
            %p
              To Comply with the Law, to Protect Ourselves, and for other Legal Purposes
            %p
              We may also share information if required by law, or to protect our rights and the safety of our users, including cooperating with authorities in legal investigations.
            %div{ class: "text-secondary lg:text-[1.8rem] text-[1.8rem] font-lato font-normal my-5"} 
              Third-Party Resources
            %p
              Chesed Train may contain links to other websites or resources on the internet. When you access third-party websites, you do so at your own risk. These websites are not under Chesed Train’s control, and you acknowledge that Chesed Train is not liable for the functions or any other aspect of those websites or resources. You agree that Chesed Train shall not be liable for any damage that may result from your use of a third-party resource or website.
            %div{ class: "text-secondary lg:text-[1.8rem] text-[1.8rem] font-lato font-normal my-5"} 
              Data Security
            %p
              We implement reasonable measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, disclosure, or misuse. While we strive to secure your data, please be aware that no method of internet transmission is completely secure. In the event of a data breach, we will notify affected users promptly and take necessary steps to mitigate any potential harm.
            %div{ class: "text-secondary lg:text-[1.8rem] text-[1.8rem] font-lato font-normal my-5"} 
              Your Rights and Choices
            %p
              You can access, update, or delete your personal information at any time by contacting us. You can also opt out of promotional communications, though we may still send you essential service-related messages. You have the right to request a copy of the information we hold about you, and to ask for corrections if the information is inaccurate.
            %div{ class: "text-secondary lg:text-[1.8rem] text-[1.8rem] font-lato font-normal my-5"} 
              Children’s Privacy
            %p
              Chesed Train’s Services are designed for a general audience and are not intended for children under 16. If we learn that we have inadvertently collected information from a child under 16, we will promptly delete it. If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us.
            %div{ class: "text-secondary lg:text-[1.8rem] text-[1.8rem] font-lato font-normal my-5"} 
              International Users
            %p
              If you access our Services from outside the United States, your information may be transferred to and processed in the U.S. By using our Services, you consent to such transfer and processing, and you acknowledge that U.S. data protection laws may differ from those in your country.
            %div{ class: "text-secondary lg:text-[1.8rem] text-[1.8rem] font-lato font-normal my-5"} 
              Changes to This Policy
            %p
              We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. When we make significant updates, we will notify you by posting a prominent notice on our Website and updating the “Last Updated” date at the top of this Policy.
            %div{ class: "text-secondary lg:text-[1.8rem] text-[1.8rem] font-lato font-normal my-5"} 
              Contact Us
            %p
              For any questions or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
            %p
              Chesed Train Inc. 407 Lincoln Rd. Suite 6H - Box 7168, Miami Beach, FL 33139
            %p
              Email: info@chesedtrain.com
